# Coding Rules

Always reuse widgets.

Never duplicate code.

Use ThemeExtensions.

Keep widgets small.

Refactor shared components first.

No magic numbers.

Document complex logic.

Leave code cleaner than you found it.

Preserve functionality.

Do not continue to the next phase without approval.

---

# Before finishing a phase verify:

- No overflow
- No clipped text
- No duplicated components
- No inconsistent padding
- Accessibility
- Localization
- RTL

# These rules apply to every phase.

• Never redesign the app.
• Preserve the navy and gold branding.
• Preserve all existing functionality.
• Reuse shared components.
• Refactor instead of duplicating.
• Do not introduce temporary fixes.
• Do not continue to the next phase without my approval.
• If a change belongs in a shared widget, update the shared widget instead of individual screens.
• Leave the codebase cleaner than you found it.
• Prioritize readability, maintainability, and consistency.

# UI POLISH ROADMAP — "Premium Pass"

Source: App Store reviewer audit of `app-ui-screenshots/` (2026-07-12).
Goal: remove every "unfinished" tell WITHOUT redesigning the app. The navy/gold
identity, pill silhouettes, rounded cards, tier gamification, rings, and
facepiles all stay. This roadmap only enforces discipline and consistency.

Companion docs (apply to every phase):
- `docs/Rules.md` — global phase rules (never redesign, preserve functionality)
- `docs/before-finishing-phase.md` — exit checklist (overflow, clipping, a11y, RTL, l10n)
- Verification for each phase: `flutter analyze` clean, `flutter test` green,
  `flutter gen-l10n` after any `.arb` change, manual device check of touched screens.

**Gate: each phase ends with a review + explicit approval before the next begins.**

