## Phase 2 — One form-field system + safe areas

**Why:** four labeling systems coexist (placeholder-only, amber headers, white bold,
floating labels). Placeholder-as-label also fails accessibility — the label
disappears while typing. Register's CTA sits under the Android gesture bar.

Tasks:
- [ ] Extend `core/widgets/branded_text_field.dart`: persistent small label ABOVE the filled navy field (the Min Age/Max Age pattern already in Create Session — promote it app-wide). Placeholder becomes a hint only ("cm", "kg", "you@email.com").
- [ ] Multiline variant: hint text top-left aligned, not vertically centered (announcement Message box).
- [ ] Migrate every form: Sign In, Register, Create Session, Quick Session, Recurring Session, New Announcement, dialogs (`set_profile_basics_dialog.dart`, `edit_body_metrics_dialog.dart`).
- [ ] One label style rule: field labels from the shared widget; section headers use the amber caps eyebrow token from Phase 0. Kill the white-bold/amber alternation in Create Session.
- [ ] `SafeArea`/padding on bottom CTAs (Register button vs gesture bar).

Files: `core/widgets/branded_text_field.dart`, all form screens above.
Accept when: every text field in the app is the same component with a visible label
while typing; Register CTA fully above the gesture bar; RTL checked.

