## Phase 3 — One selector component (chips)

**Why:** three patterns for single-choice: detached pills (Leaderboard/History/Players),
attached segmented control (announcement Audience), assorted outline chips of varying
heights (Register gender, Create Session gender/coaches). Same interaction, three languages.

Tasks:
- [ ] Generalize `core/widgets/gender_filter_chips.dart` into an `AppChoiceChips` component (fixed height, amber fill = selected, navy outline = idle, optional icon + label — never icon-only: ♂/♀ get text labels or semantic labels).
- [ ] Replace: announcement Audience segmented control; Register Male/Female; Create Session Male/Female/Mixed; coach selector (give it a REAL selected state — currently invisible); This Month/All Time on Leaderboard.
- [ ] Keep `gender_filter_chips` API as a thin wrapper so existing call sites stay small.

Files: `core/widgets/gender_filter_chips.dart` (→ generalized), announcement composer,
`register_screen.dart`, `create_session_screen.dart`, leaderboard screen.
Accept when: exactly one chip silhouette exists app-wide; selected state visible on
every selector including coaches; all chips have text or semantic labels.

