## Phase 4 — Layout collisions & session-card hierarchy

**Why:** the FAB covers the second session card's capacity number; lists end flush
under FAB/nav; the home screen says "2 upcoming sessions" twice; joined sessions
render twice (hero + list); two unlabeled ratios per card (waitlist 0/6 vs capacity 7/12).

Tasks:
- [ ] Global: bottom padding (~96dp token) on every scrollable that sits under the FAB or `floating_nav_bar.dart`.
- [ ] `session_card.dart`: one labeled primary ratio (people icon + "7/12" + thin capacity bar); waitlist collapses to a small pill shown ONLY when non-empty; drop the hourglass mystery ratio.
- [ ] Fade decorative art (volleyballs/cat) to ~15% opacity behind text/facepile zones via a navy gradient scrim inside the card.
- [ ] Sessions tab: delete the "2 upcoming sessions" summary card (the greeting + UPCOMING header already carry it); when the Next-Up hero shows a session, compress its list entry (slim "JOINED ✓" row) or drop it.
- [ ] Countdown: hide the SEC cell when >1h remains ("Starts in 4h 31m" chip style already exists on the hero) — also stops per-second rebuilds.

Files: `core/widgets/session_card.dart`, `sessions_tab.dart`, session detail screens,
`core/widgets/floating_nav_bar.dart` (exposes its height for padding).
Accept when: nothing is ever occluded by FAB/nav; each card has exactly one ratio
with a label; no duplicate representation of the same session on one screen.

