## Phase 5 — Roster UX & session lifecycle states

**Why:** red remove-attendee icons sit on every row permanently (even on ended
sessions); empty attendance circles look like radio buttons; "Cancel" in red at the
app-bar reads as navigation; a finished session shows an alarming red "Session Full"
chip and red bar; attendance is signaled twice per row.

Tasks:
- [ ] Edit mode: the existing pencil toggles the roster into edit state; red person-minus icons render ONLY in edit mode. Ended sessions: no remove icons at all.
- [ ] Replace the unlabeled double-check icon with a labeled outline-chip button ("Mark all") using the Phase 3 component style.
- [ ] Move "Cancel" out of the app bar → explicit "Cancel session" red-outline button (Sign Out style) in the detail body, behind `confirm_dialog.dart`.
- [ ] Completed sessions: "Session Full" chip hidden once ended; capacity bar switches to success green; ONE attendance indicator per row (keep avatar badge, drop trailing check); anchor "No endorsements left" text inside the attendees header, not floating.
- [ ] Attendance circles hidden for player viewers (viewer-aware, coach-only affordance).

Files: session detail / completed session screens, roster row widget,
`core/widgets/confirm_dialog.dart`, `attendee_facepile.dart` if rings change.
Accept when: no destructive control visible outside edit mode; ended sessions read
as celebration (green), not alarm (red); players never see coach-only controls.

