## Phase 6 — Status system & glow budget

**Why:** membership status wears three costumes on Players (amber outline 2-line,
solid glowing LIFETIME, green outline Active) and shouts louder than the player's
name. Glow is everywhere (hero, LIFETIME, milestone thumb, Rookie badge, rings),
so nothing feels special.

Tasks:
- [ ] One membership chip: same pill geometry always; color = state (green outline active, amber outline expiring w/ "2d left" second line, solid amber lifetime). Quieter than the player name.
- [ ] Glow budget — ONE glowing element per screen: keep Next-Up hero (Sessions) and LIFETIME (Players). Flatten milestone-track thumb, Rookie/achievement badge glows, avatar-ring glows to plain amber strokes (`ringed_avatar.dart`, `level_badge.dart`).
- [ ] Profile milestone track: remove the slider-thumb look — filled progress line with tick dots at 5/20/50/100 (progress, not a draggable).
- [ ] Verify & fix the duplicated Details/Gender/Account block on the profile screen (reproduce on device; screenshot may be a stitch artifact — if real, it's the first fix of the phase).
- [ ] Add Photo circle (Register): amber dashed ring + camera icon so it reads as tappable.

Files: `players_tab.dart` + player card widget, `ringed_avatar.dart`, `level_badge.dart`,
`profile_tab.dart`, `profile_stat_cards.dart`, `register_screen.dart`.
Accept when: one chip system for membership; ≤1 glow per screen; profile renders
each section exactly once.

