## Phase 7 — Leaderboard clarity, accessibility & RTL final pass

**Why:** the podium shows five large numerals whose meanings alternate (rank vs
score) and never names the metric; ties (2,2,2 → ranks 1,2,3) look arbitrary.
Secondary gray-on-navy text sits at/below WCAG 4.5:1; micro-labels are ~10sp caps;
mixed AR/EN announcement text renders scrambled (missing bidi isolation).

Tasks:
- [ ] Leaderboard: amber caps eyebrow naming the metric ("GAMES THIS MONTH"); score pills get the small volleyball icon so score ≠ rank at a glance; ties share a rank ("=1"); current user's row ringed with the amber stroke; list avatars get the same ring treatment as the rest of the app.
- [ ] Contrast pass using Phase 0 tokens: secondary text ≥ ~75% white; micro caps labels ≥ 11sp; verify amber-on-navy and green-over-art spots.
- [ ] Bidi: wrap user-generated content (announcement title/body, names) in Unicode isolates / resolved `Directionality` so embedded English stops shredding Arabic sentences.
- [ ] Semantics: labels/tooltips on every icon-only button (toolbar download/whistle/trophy/bell, edit, delete); move coach-only toolbar extras into a labeled overflow menu if crowded.
- [ ] Announcement card: quarantine the trash icon (overflow menu or edit-mode reveal) instead of exposed low-contrast destructive icon next to the title.
- [ ] Final sweep: run `docs/before-finishing-phase.md` checklist against EVERY screen in `app-ui-screenshots/`, both locales, RTL, small device (360dp).

Files: leaderboard screen, announcements screens, `core/theme/app_theme.dart` tokens,
toolbar rows in `sessions_tab.dart` / `players_tab.dart`.
Accept when: metric named on leaderboard; ties honest; WCAG AA for text; VoiceOver/
TalkBack can name every control; mixed-direction text renders correctly.

