## Phase order rationale

0→1→2→3 are the "unfinished tells" (tokens, plurals, truncation, one field, one chip)
— roughly 60% of audit findings, near-zero redesign risk. 4→5 fix layout collisions
and destructive-action hygiene. 6→7 are refinement: status system, glow restraint,
leaderboard, accessibility. 8 (coaches screen, added 2026-07-12) is an independent
screen-level pass — it only needs Phase 0 tokens, so it can be pulled earlier if the
coaches screen becomes a priority. Each phase is independently shippable and reviewed
against `docs/Rules.md` before approval.